message.content:
Explanation:

- The controller method handling GET /v1/posts/{post}/comments is index(Request $request, Post $post). It returns CommentResource::collection(...->paginate($request->input('limit', 20))). Therefore:
  - There is a path parameter {post} (route-model-bound Post, treated as an integer identifier).
  - There is an optional query parameter limit (integer) with a default of 20 used for pagination.
  - The response is a paginated JSON ResourceCollection using Laravel's paginator structure (data, links, meta).
  - Each item in data is formatted by App\Http\Resources\Comment and includes these properties:
    - id (integer)
    - content (string)
    - posted_at (ISO 8601 date-time string)
    - humanized_posted_at (string)
    - author_id (integer)
    - post_id (integer)
    - author_name (string)
    - author_url (string, URL)
    - can_delete (boolean)
  - The paginator includes links (object of URLs) and meta (pagination metadata fields such as current_page, from, last_page, per_page, to, total, path).

- The endpoint does not require authentication in the controller signature; the Comment resource uses Auth::guard('sanctum')->user() only to compute can_delete, so can_delete may be false for anonymous requests.

